rComments: Great guy, hilarious sense of humor, super smart!  Had us all over for pizza, which was nice.  He always jokes that he's not smart enough to be teaching an honors class like this, though clearly he is a genius!
One of the smartest men I've ever met - and he had the class to his house for homemade pizza, too.  Learning from the brightest is always a great experience, so take his class if possible.
He was the best teacher I have ever had.  If you ever get the chance, you should definitely take his class.  He is so excited about the subject and really helpful and nice.
This man is the most supportive teacher/person that I have ever encountered.  He believed in me when I didn't even believe in myself.  I owe all of my successes to him.  Thanks.
